Which Minecraft versions are supported? The plugin is optimized for 1.20.x+ versions on Paper and Purpur engines.

Can I disable the Math Captcha? Yes, it can be toggled on or off at any time in the config.yml.

How can a player change their password? By using the /changepassword <old> <new> command after a successful login.

What happens after multiple failed login attempts? The Strike System will automatically trigger a Security Lock to prevent Brute-Force attacks.

Do I need a Discord Bot for Webhooks? No, the plugin sends data directly via the Webhook URL â€“ no extra bots required.

Can I customize in-game messages? Yes, PureAuth allows full customization of all messages in the configuration files.

What happens if I change my IP with Auto-Login enabled? The IP-Trust system detects the change and prompts for a password. Once logged in, the new IP is saved as trusted.

Can an admin change a player's password? Yes, admins can use the console command: /pureauth setpassword <player> <new_password>.

Which databases are supported? You can choose between local SQLite (zero config) or MySQL/MariaDB for larger networks.

Are passwords in the database secure? Yes, all passwords are one-way encrypted using BCrypt industry standards.

Does this plugin require ProtocolLib? No. PureAuth is fully standalone and uses a custom IP-Trust system.

How does Premium Auto-Login work? The plugin verifies your account via Mojang API. If you join from a trusted IP, you are logged in automatically. If your IP changes, a password is required for security.

What if I lose my 2FA device? For security reasons, only a Server Administrator can reset your 2FA using a dedicated console command.

Does it affect server performance? No. Using HikariCP, all database operations (MySQL/SQLite) are handled asynchronously, ensuring zero impact on server TPS.
